text: You need to remove the water source blocks from the side that you want exposed. It's kinda hard to communicate exactly how Minecraft water physics works, but if you make the flowing water will flow down unless it has a block underneath it, in which it'll flow outwards one block. So if you put source blocks only at the top of the mouth of the cave and then push the mouth back one block, it should let the water make a vertical wall. To prevent the water from spreading across the floor of the cave, just leave a little divot right where the water falls in to. If it's already started flowing into the floor, you can temporarily put a 1 block high barrier to cut the flow, dig the little indent, and then remove the blocks. The water won't start flowing out onto the floor again, because it's already fallen into the divot and it won't spread outward from the middle of a stream, it only does that at the bottom of it.
